    <briefdescription>
<para>Features that implement in C++ the GLSL specification as closely as possible. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The GLM core consists of <ref refid="group__core__types" kindref="compound">C++ types that mirror GLSL types</ref> and C++ functions that mirror the GLSL functions. It also includes <ref refid="group__core__precision" kindref="compound">a set of qualifier-based types</ref> that can be used in the appropriate functions. The C++ types are all based on a basic set of <ref refid="group__core__template" kindref="compound">template types</ref>.</para>
<para>The best documentation for GLM Core is the current GLSL specification, <ulink url="http://www.opengl.org/registry/doc/GLSLangSpec.4.20.8.clean.pdf">version 4.2 (pdf file)</ulink>.</para>
<para>GLM core functionalities require &lt;<ref refid="glm_8hpp" kindref="compound">glm/glm.hpp</ref>&gt; to be included to be used. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
